It even says ねとりover the “NTR” in the title page. Idk why I gotta explain this shit, but here: 寝取る (Netoru) means ‘to steal someone’s lover.’ Specifically, it’s taking the active role, as in “[I] stole their girlfriend.” Everyone saying NTR as in someone being cucked is a whole different genre technically. That’s 寝取られ(Netorare) which is the passive form of the verb, as in “[someone] stole MY lover.” I mean, I get that most of you aren’t interested in studying Japanese, but like at least look up what tags mean.
